{"word":"H5411 - נָתִין - Nâthîyn - naw-theen' - Nethinims","slug":"H5411","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָתִין</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Nâthîyn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-theen'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Nethinims"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05EA;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05DF;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E0;&#x05EA;&#x05D9;&#x05DF;</b><sup></bdo>o</sup> - <b>na&#x0302;th&#x0131;&#x0302;yn  na&#x0302;thu&#x0302;n</b> - <i>naw-theen', naw-thoon'</i><p/>The second form is the proper form, as passive participle; from <a href=\"#/H5414\">H5414</a>; one <i>given</i>, that is, (in the plural only) the <i>Nethinim</i>, or Temple Servants (as <i>given</i> up to that duty): - Nethinims."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4976\">H4976</a>, <a href=\"#/H4977\">H4977</a>, <a href=\"#/H4979\">H4979</a>, <a href=\"#/H4980\">H4980</a>, <a href=\"#/H4982\">H4982</a>, <a href=\"#/H4983\">H4983</a>, <a href=\"#/H4991\">H4991</a>, <a href=\"#/H4992\">H4992</a>, <a href=\"#/H4993\">H4993</a>, <a href=\"#/H5414\">H5414</a>, <a href=\"#/H5416\">H5416</a>, <a href=\"#/H5417\">H5417</a>, <a href=\"#/H5418\">H5418</a>, <a href=\"#/H5419\">H5419</a>"}]}